Ticket: - Read the instructions carefully and then you start working on it





Ticket

Create a directory Linux in your home directory
cd
mkdir Linux
cd Linux
Create two file linuxdis1.txt and linuxdis2.txt
touch linuxdis1.txt linuxdis2.txt
In Linuxdis1.txt put content-1 and content-2 in linuxdis2.txt
cat > linuxdis1.txt
A Linux distribution (often abbreviated as distro) is an operating system made from a
software collection that is based upon the Linux kernel and, often, a package
management system. Linux users usually obtain their operating system by downloading
one of the Linux distributions, which are available for a wide variety of systems ranging
from embedded devices

cat > linuxdis2.txt
There are commecially-backed distributions, such as Fedora (Red
Hat), openSUSE (SUSE) and Ubuntu (Canonical Ltd.), and entirely community-driven
distributions, such as Debian, Slackware, Gentoo and Arch Linux.

Using wc command count number of line, words and byte in linuxdis1.txt
wc linuxdis1.txt
Using wc command count number of line, words and byte in linuxdis2.txt
wc linuxdis2.txt
Using wc command count number of line, words and byte in linuxdis1.txt and linuxdis2.txt together
wc linuxdis1.txt linuxdis2.txt
Now display only number of words in linuxdis1.txt
wc -w linuxdis1.txt | awk '{print $1}'
Display number of line in linuxdis1.txt
wc -l linuxdis1.txt | awk '{print $1}'



